    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Steering Gear Adjusting Screw and Retainer Assembly</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the adjusting screw has been removed, coat the expanded end of the new adjusting screw
                with a suitable grade of wheel bearing grease and insert into the recess in the end of the sector shaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1102093" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figdg0/Dg0449a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>Stake the retainer securely into the sector shaft slots. If the retainer is broken or cracked
                    during the staking, install a new retainer. Failure to do so can result in the loss of manual and
                    power steering control.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thread a new sector shaft screw retainer into the sector shaft, tighten and then stake the
                retainer in the 2 slots provided.
            </para>
            <para>&#8226; The adjusting screw must rotate freely by hand, with very little end play, 0.05 mm
                (0.000-0.002 inch).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1102094" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figdg0/Dg0450a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
    </svcsubproc>
